table.name: order_movement
table.description: Order movement represent part of the routing of an order. It is also a collection of ship units that are unplanned for certain part of a route.

columns.name: ORDER_MOVEMENT_GID
columns.description: The GID for the order movement.

columns.name: ORDER_MOVEMENT_XID
columns.description: The XID for the order movement.

columns.name: ORDER_RELEASE_GID
columns.description: The order release GID that is the parent for the order movement.

columns.name: IS_TEMPORARY
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether this order movement can coexist with shipments. If this flag is true, the order movement will be removed once the order movement is planned on shipments. Otherwise the order movement's status is set to PLANNED-FINAL and stays in the system.

columns.name: CREATION_PROCESS_TYPE
columns.description: The creation process type, examples are from an itinerary (SYSTEM-ITINERARY) or from a shipment (SYSTEM-ACTIONS).

columns.name: SEQ_NO
columns.description: The sequence number used to define where in the order release delivery path the order movement resides.

columns.name: PERSPECTIVE
columns.description: Indicates whether this order movement is part of the buy or sell perspective and hence the associated shipments.

columns.name: SOURCE_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The source of the order movement and it can be null for the planning logic to determine the best one.

columns.name: IS_FIXED_SRC
columns.description: Indicates whether the source location on this order movement is the real source location or it is derived from the source location of its upstream shipments.

columns.name: DEST_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The destination of the order movement and it can be null for the planning logic to determine the best one.

columns.name: IS_FIXED_DEST
columns.description: Indicates whether the destination location on this order movement is the real source location or it is derived from the source location of its upstream shipments.

columns.name: EARLY_PICKUP_DATE
columns.description: The earliest pickup of this order movement.

columns.name: OPERATION_EARLY_PICKUP_DATE
columns.description: The date is calculated from upstream shipments' end time.

columns.name: LATE_PICKUP_DATE
columns.description: The latest pickup time of this order movement.

columns.name: EARLY_DELIVERY_DATE
columns.description: The earliest delivery of this order movement.

columns.name: LATE_DELIVERY_DATE
columns.description: The latest delivery of this order movement.

columns.name: OPERATION_LATE_DELIVERY_DATE
columns.description: This date is calculated from downstream shipments' start time.

columns.name: REUSE_EQUIPMENT
columns.description: The reuse equipment flag indicating that the order movement will use the shipment equipment record from the previous leg. This is initially taken from the itinerary if the order movement was created from one.

columns.name: PARENT_SOURCE_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The parent order movement source location ID if this is a child order movement built from network planning engine.

columns.name: PARENT_DEST_LOCATION_GID
columns.description: The parent order movement destination location ID if this is a child order movement built from network planning engine.

columns.name: ORIGINAL_LEG_GID
columns.description: The original leg ID from the itinerary associated to the original leg position.

columns.name: ORIGINAL_LEG_POSITION
columns.description: The position of the original leg. The main leg's leg position is 0. Legs left to the main leg have positions -1, -2, etc. Legs right to the main leg have positions 1, 2, etc.

columns.name: BULK_PLAN_GID
columns.description: The bulk plan GID if this order movement was created through a bulk planning run.

columns.name: ORIGINAL_SELL_OM_GID
columns.description: The original buy order movement GID used if the order movement is split for additional planning.

columns.name: TOTAL_SHIP_UNIT_COUNT
columns.description: The total ship unit count for this order movement. Can be 1 for a discrete item or greater if it is modeling a bulk count order.

columns.name: TOTAL_WEIGHT
columns.description: The total weight for this order movement.

columns.name: TOTAL_WEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total weight unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_WEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The total weight in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_VOLUME
columns.description: The total volume for this order movement.

columns.name: TOTAL_VOLUME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The total volume unit of measure.

columns.name: TOTAL_VOLUME_BASE
columns.description: The total volume in the base unit of measure.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED1_ICON_GID
columns.description: Stores a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes for the object.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED2_ICON_GID
columns.description: Stores a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes for the object.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED3_ICON_GID
columns.description: Stores a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes for the object.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED4_ICON_GID
columns.description: Stores a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes for the object.

columns.name: USER_DEFINED5_ICON_GID
columns.description: Stores a user-defined icon that will appear within the user interface to help visually identify attributes for the object.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_WIDTH
columns.description: The width of the ship unit. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_WIDTH_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the ship unit width. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_WIDTH_BASE
columns.description: The ship unit width in base units. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_LENGTH
columns.description: The length of the ship unit. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_LENGTH_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for ship unit length. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_LENGTH_BASE
columns.description: The ship unit length in base units. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_HEIGHT
columns.description: The height of the ship unit. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_HEIGHT_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for ship unit height. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_HEIGHT_BASE
columns.description: The ship unit height in base units. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_DIAMETER
columns.description: The diameter of the ship unit. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_DIAMETER_UOM_CODE
columns.description: The unit of measure for the ship unit diameter. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: SHIP_UNIT_DIAMETER_BASE
columns.description: The ship unit diameter in base units. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: TRANSPORT_HANDLING_UNIT_GID
columns.description: The transport handling unit. This column will show value only if the order movement has one ship unit.

columns.name: INDICATOR
columns.description: A definable indicator for the order movement.

columns.name: PICKUP_ROUTING_SEQUENCE_GID
columns.description: This routing sequence identifier applies for the source location of that specific order movement and will override any order release routing sequence information at these location.

columns.name: DROPOFF_ROUTING_SEQUENCE_GID
columns.description: This routing sequence identifier applies for the source location of that specific order movement and will override any order release routing sequence information at these location.

columns.name: PRIORITY
columns.description: The priority associated with an order movement.

columns.name: SOURCE_TAG
columns.description: The tag value for the source location of the order movement.

columns.name: DEST_TAG
columns.description: The tag value for the destination location of the order movement.

columns.name: SHIPMENT_GID
columns.description: The shipment GID associated to the order movement if it is scheduled on a shipment.

columns.name: DOMAIN_NAME
columns.description: The database domain where this data is stored.

columns.name: INSERT_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data insert user.

columns.name: INSERT_DATE
columns.description: The date and time of data insert.

columns.name: UPDATE_USER
columns.description: The user ID of the data update user.

columns.name: UPDATE_DATE
columns.description: Date and time of the most recent data update.

columns.name: MODE_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The mode profile identifier contains the unique identifier for the mode profile for the leg.

columns.name: EQUIPMENT_GROUP_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The equipment group GID contains the GID for the equipment group profile for the leg.

columns.name: CALCULATE_SERVICE_TIME
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether to calculate the service time when creating the shipment for this order movement. Initially derived from the itinerary.

columns.name: CALCULATE_CONTRACTED_RATE
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether to calculate the service time when creating the shipment for this order movement. Initially derived from the itinerary.

columns.name: EXPECTED_TRANSIT_TIME
columns.description: Expected transit time contains the expected time for this leg of the shipment to take.

columns.name: EXPECTED_TRANSIT_TIME_BASE
columns.description: Expected transit time in base unit of measure.

columns.name: EXPECTED_TRANSIT_TIME_UOM_CODE
columns.description: Expected transit time unit of measure.

columns.name: EXPECTED_COST
columns.description: Expected cost contains the expected cost for the leg.

columns.name: EXPECTED_COST_BASE
columns.description: Expected cost in the base currency.

columns.name: EXPECTED_COST_CURRENCY_GID
columns.description: Expected cost currency contains the currency for the expected cost of the leg.

columns.name: RATE_OFFERING_GID
columns.description: The rate offering GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: RATE_GEO_GID
columns.description: The rate detail GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: EQUIPMENT_GROUP_GID
columns.description: The equipment group GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: TRANSPORT_MODE_GID
columns.description: The transport mode GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: SERVPROV_GID
columns.description: The service provider GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: SERVPROV_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The service provider profile GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: RATE_SERVICE_PROFILE_GID
columns.description: The rate service profile GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: IS_TEMPLATE
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether this order movement is to be used as a template.

columns.name: SHIP_WITH_GROUP
columns.description: The ship with group GID constraint for the order movement.

columns.name: LEG_CLASSIFICATION_GID
columns.description: The leg classification is used for order movement group building. The order movements plan and match to the itinerary leg classification value.

columns.name: LEG_CONSOLIDATION_GROUP_GID
columns.description: The planning engine sets the leg consolidation group based on rules around the leg classification value.

columns.name: IS_NETWORK_ROUTABLE
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether this order movement can be planned using the network routing model.

columns.name: ROUTING_CONSTRAINT_GID
columns.description: The routing constraint identifier shows the routing constraints that apply to this order movement and is only used when is network routable is set to true.

columns.name: IS_ROUTING_FIXED
columns.description: A Y/N indicator for whether the routing constraints are fixed during subsequent planning actions.
